# Shell environment reference  (template — replace with your own)

Copy this file to `SKILL.md` (the installer does this if it's missing) and document your environment
so the agent stops guessing. Keep it factual and concise. Suggested structure:

## OS & shell
- OS: `<macOS / Windows / Linux>`
- Shell: `<zsh / PowerShell / bash>` + prompt/plugin manager if any
- Package manager: `<Homebrew / winget / scoop / apt>` + prefix/path

## Aliases (interactive shell only — in Bash-tool calls use the REAL binary)
| Alias | Real command | Notes |
|-------|--------------|-------|
| `ll`  | `eza -la --git` | example — replace with yours, or delete the table |

> If you alias common commands (`ls`/`cat`/`find`/`grep` → modern tools), those aliases do **not**
> apply in non-interactive Bash-tool calls — call the real binary by name.

## Installed CLI tools the agent should assume you have
- `<git, gh, ripgrep (rg), fd, jq, uv, ...>`

## Shell plugins / extras
- `<autosuggestions, syntax-highlighting, fzf, zoxide, ...>`
